<PageTitle>Brouter - A modern, declarative, nestable router for Blazor</PageTitle>

@* The marketing landing page: hero → proof strip → feature grid → code walkthrough →
   comparison with the built-in Router → persona CTAs → FAQ → final CTA. Docs live under
   /docs (DocsShell); live demos under /playground. *@

<div class="bb-landing">

    @* ============================== Hero ============================== *@

    <section class="bb-hero">
        <div class="bb-hero-copy">
            <span class="bb-hero-eyebrow">Open source · MIT · net8.0 / net9.0 / net10.0</span>
            <h1>Routing for Blazor,<br /><span class="bb-hero-accent">done right!</span></h1>
            <p class="bb-hero-sub">
                Brouter is a modern, declarative, nestable router with everything today's router
                libraries are measured by: async guards, data loaders with stale-while-revalidate
                caching, keep-alive, view transitions, and compile-time-safe URLs - while your
                existing <code>&#64;page</code> components keep working unchanged.
            </p>
            <pre class="bb-code bb-hero-install"><span class="c"># the router</span>
dotnet add package Bit.Brouter
<span class="c"># optional: typed, compile-time-safe URL builders</span>
dotnet add package Bit.Brouter.Generators</pre>
            <div class="bb-hero-actions">
                <BrouterLink Href="/docs/getting-started" class="btn btn-primary bb-btn-lg">Get started →</BrouterLink>
                <BrouterLink Href="/playground" class="btn btn-outline bb-btn-lg">Live playground</BrouterLink>
                <a class="btn btn-outline bb-btn-lg" href="https://github.com/bitfoundation/bitplatform" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="bb-hero-code">
            <pre class="bb-code"><span class="c">@@* App.razor - routes are components, so nesting is just markup *@@</span>
&lt;<span class="k">Brouter</span> NotFoundUrl=<span class="s">"404"</span> AppAssembly=<span class="s">"@@GetType().Assembly"</span>&gt;
    &lt;<span class="k">Broute</span> Path=<span class="s">"/"</span> Component=<span class="s">"@@typeof(HomePage)"</span> /&gt;

    &lt;<span class="k">Broute</span> Path=<span class="s">"/users/{id:int}"</span>
            Guard=<span class="s">"@@RequireSignIn"</span>
            Loader=<span class="s">"@@LoadUser"</span>
            StaleTime=<span class="s">"@@TimeSpan.FromMinutes(1)"</span>&gt;
        &lt;<span class="k">Content</span>&gt;&lt;UserPage /&gt;&lt;/<span class="k">Content</span>&gt;
        &lt;<span class="k">Routes</span>&gt;
            &lt;<span class="k">Broute</span> Path=<span class="s">"/orders"</span> Component=<span class="s">"@@typeof(OrdersPage)"</span> /&gt;
        &lt;/<span class="k">Routes</span>&gt;
